usinessinsider.com%2Fboomer-retirement-south-korea-germany-affordable-healthcare-travel-military-veteran-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emilitary%20veterans%20who%20moved%20abroad%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20of%202022%2C%20132%20US%20Navy%20veterans%20lived%20in%20Thailand%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.defense.gov%2F2023%2FOct%2F06%2F2003315292%2F-1%2F-1%2F0%2FMRS%2520STATRPT%25202022%2520V999.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Defense%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20October%202023.%20While%20the%20report%20didn't%20include%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereasons%20for%20why%20veterans%20left%20the%20US%2C%20Simms-Aur%20said%20he%20wanted%20a%20better%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20the%20opportunity%20to%20travel%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThailand%20was%20the%20sixth-most%20popular%20country%20for%20Navy%20veterans%2C%20following%20the%20Philippines%2C%20Japan%2C%20Italy%2C%20Spain%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Kingdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224dfada27-c237-433d-bdc4-bd5fadef9a80%5C%22%3EThailand%20offers%20low%20costs%20and%20a%20good%20lifestyle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESimms-Aur%20enlisted%20in%20the%20US%20Navy%20when%20he%20was%2021.%20He%20said%20he%20wanted%20a%20better%20economic%20opportunity%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20take%20out%20loans%20for%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20researched%20a%20lot%20of%20stuff%20about%20finance%20because%20I%20don't%20come%20from%20wealth%2C%26quot%3B%20Simms-Aur%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20wanted%20to%20change%20the%20trajectory%20of%20my%20family's%20financial%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimms-Aur%20served%20for%20three%20years%2C%20and%20after%20he%20was%20honorably%20discharged%2C%20he%20said%20he%20realized%20how%20expensive%20it%20was%20to%20live%20in%20the%20US.%20He%20was%20receiving%20veteran%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20but%20declined%20to%20elaborate%20on%20what%20type%20%E2%80%94%20and%20worked%20in%20IT%2C%20but%20felt%20like%