n%20India%20-%20Maulana%20Masood%20Azhar%20(founder%20of%20terror%20outfit%20Jaish-e-Mohammed)%20and%20Mushtaq%20Ahmed%20Zargar%20(Al%20Umar%20Mujahideen).%20But%20except%20the%20police%20and%20intelligence%20agencies%2C%20only%20a%20few%20had%20heard%20of%20the%20third%20person%3A%20Omar%20Saeed%20Sheikh.%20Just%20two%20years%20later%2C%20Sheikh%20would%20become%20infamous%20worldwide%20for%20kidnapping%20and%20beheading%20a%20US%20journalist.%20He%20also%20nearly%20caused%20a%20diplomatic%20crisis%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20following%20the%20November%2026%20terror%20attacks%20in%20Mumbai%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Kidnapping%20Of%203%20Westerners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Netflix%20web%20series%20%3Cem%3EIC%20814%3A%20The%20Kandahar%20Hijack%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20sparked%20a%20controversy%20over%20names%20and%20the%20portrayal%20of%20a%20few%20of%20the%20hijackers.%20But%20it%20has%20taken%20me%20back%20to%20my%20chance%20encounter%20with%20Sheikh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%20was%201994.%20My%20cameraman%20and%20I%20were%20out%20to%20cover%20a%20story%20for%20a%20Delhi-based%20TV%20channel%3B%20it%20was%20going%20through%20dry%20runs%20before%20the%20launch.%20We%20had%20barely%20reached%20Ghaziabad%20when%20we%20witnessed%20elaborate%20security%20arrangements%20outside%20a%20private%20hospital.%20The%20road%20was%20cordoned%20off.%20We%20were%20told%20that%20a%20terrorist%20was%20admitted%20to%20the%20hospital%20after%20being%20wounded%20in%20a%20police%20encounter%20in%20Saharanpur%20the%20previous%20night%2C%20during%20which%20a%20police%20inspector%20had%20been%20shot%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecurity%20was%20tighter%20inside%20the%20hospital.%20But%20some%20smooth-talking%20with%20an%20amiable%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20'%3Cem%3Edaroga%20ji%3C%2Fem%3E'%20did%20the%20trick.%20He%20allowed%20us%20in%20on%20the%20condition%20that%20we%20would%20brief%20him%20on%20our%20conversation%20with%20the%20man%20inside%2C%20Omar%20Sheikh%2C%20whose%20English%20accent%2C%20he%20admitted%2C%20he%20did%20not%20understand.%20We%20rolled%20the%20camera%20as%20we%20entered%20the%20room%2C%20not%20knowing%20who%20Sheikh%20was%20and%20how%20big%20a%20catch%20he%20was%20for%20the%20police.%20The%20only%20piece%20of%20information%20we%20had%20was%20that%20the%20injured%20man%20had%20kidnapped%20three%20Britons%20and%20an%20American%20in%20Delhi%20and%20hid%20them%20in%20a%20house%20in%20Saharanpur%20on%20their%20way%20to%20Kashmir.%20He%20had%20told%20his%20captives%20that%20his%20name%20was%20Rohit%20Sharma%2C%20and%20that%20he%20was%20taking%20them%20to%20his%20quaint%20ancestral%20village%20in%20Kashmir.%20But%20when%20a%20Saharanpur%20police%20patrol%20party%20stumbled%20upon%20the%20captives%2C%20a%20shootout%20ensued.%20A%20police%20inspector%20was%20killed%2C%20and%20Sheikh%20got%20injured.%20All%20the%20captives%20though%20were%20freed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOmar%20Sheikh%2C%20The%20London-Born%2C%20LSE-Educated%20Terrorist%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hospital%20was%20posh%2C%20Sheikh's%20room%20big%20and%20clean.%20He%20lay%20in%20bed%20with%20a%20bandage%20around%20his%20right%20shoulder.%20The%20camera%20was%20rolling%20as%20we%20came%20face%20to%20face%20with%20a%20tall%20and%20bearded%20young%20man%2C%20propped%20up%20against%20hospital%20pillows%2C%20looking%20puzzled%20and%20befuddled.%20His%20first%20reaction%20was%20to%20shout%20a%20barrage%20of%20questions%20at%20us%2C%20%26quot%3BWho%20are%20you%2C%20why%20are%20you%20here%2C%20who%20has%20sent%20you%3F%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20asked%20for%20an%20interview%2C%20but%20he%20refused%20to%20speak%20to%20us%20in%20protest%20because%20he%20said%20he%20had%20no%20prior%20notice%20we%20were%20going%20to%20do%20an%20interview%20with%20him.%20He%20relented%20after%20I%20produced%20my%20press%20ID%20card.%20Before%20the%20interview%20began%2C%20he%20told%20us%20his%20name%20and%20that%20he%20was%2020%20years%20old.%20He%20was%20a%20student%20at%20the%20prestigious%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20(LSE).%20He%20also%20said%20he%20was%20born%20in%20London%20and%20was%20raised%20both%20there%20and%20in%20Lahore.%20His%20Pakistani%20immigrant%20parents%20lived%20in%20London%2C%20where%20they%20ran%20a%20clothes%20business.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20half-hour%20interview%2C%20Sheikh%20Omar%20looked%20extremely%20worried.%20He%20told%20me%20he%20would%20give%20anything%20to%20return%20to%20life%20in%20Britain.%20He%20also%20kept%20pleading%20with%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BBrother%2C%20take%20me%20out%20of%20here%2C%20please.%26quot%3B%20During%20the%20interview%2C%20he%20revealed%20how%20at%20the%20age%20of%2018%2C%20he%20had%20already%20done%20'jihad'%20in%20Bosnia%2C%20fighting%20alongside%20and%20on%20behalf%20of%20Bosnian%20Muslims%2C%20who%2C%20he%20said%2C%20were%20being%20butchered%20by%20the%20Serbs.%20He%20was%20strikingly%20young%20and%20his%20accent%20was%20distinctly%20British.%20I%20thought%20he%20had%20the%20gift%20of%20the%20gab.%20I%20am%20not%20surprised%20he%20managed%20to%20lure%20foreign%20tourists%20and%20later%2C%20in%202002%2C%20used%20the%20same%20trick%20to%20lure%20American%20journalist%20Daniel%20Pearl%20into%20captivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFooled%20by%20Extremists%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20recounted%20how%20he%20had%20been%20indoctrinated%20on%20the%20campus%20by%20an%20Islamist%20organisation%20that%20wanted%20to%20establish%20an%20Islamic%20society%20in%20Britain.%20He%20said%20he%20had%20been%20fooled%20by%20the%20hard-luck%20stories%20he%20had%20heard%20about%20the%20plight%20of%20Muslims%20and%20Kashmiris%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESheikh%20admitted%20that%20he%20was%20charged%20with%20kidnapping%20some%20foreign%20tourists%20to%20barter%20for%20Maulana%20Masood%20Azhar%2C%20who%20was%20then%20held%20in%20prison%20in%20India.%20He%20also%20admitted%20that%20he%20had%20been%20in%20Delhi%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month%20before%20the%20kidnapping%20and%20was%20struck%20by%20the%20religious%20freedom%20he%20saw.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20been%20told%20that%20Muslims%20in%20India%20had%20no%20religious%20rights%20and%20Kashmiri%20Muslims%20were%20being%20subjected%20to%20torture%20and%20rape%20by%20the%20Hindu%20army%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20him%2C%20if%20released%2C%20would%20he%20go%20back%20and%20tell%20people%20in%20Britain%20that%20Indian%20Muslims%20were%20free%20to%20build%20mosques%2C%20say%20prayers%2C%20and%20work%20in%20government%20offices%3F%20He%20said%20he%20would.%20He%20appeared%20repentant%2C%20but%20clearly%20not%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EMeeting%20Masood%20Azhar%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20Omar%20Sheikh%20chose%20the%20path%20of%20destruction%20was%20hard%20to%20say.%20He%20was%20exposed%20to%20Islamist%20extremism%20at%20a%20tender%20age.%20But%20that%20doesn't%20fully%20explain%20the%20path%20he%20chose%20early%20in%20his%20life.%20He%20was%20privileged.%20He%20went%20to%20the%20private%20Forest%20School%20in%20London%20-%20the%20same%20school%20former%20cricketer%20Nasser%20Hussain%20studied%20in.%20But%20while%20Sheikh%20became%20a%20terrorist%2C%20Hussain%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20captain%20of%20the%20England%20cricket%20team.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20LSE%2C%20Sheikh%20was%20known%20for%20his%20academic%20brilliance%2C%20especially%20in%20maths%20and%20economics.%20But%20he%20dropped%20out%20before%20completing%20his%20degree%20to%20join%20the%20'jihad'%20in%20Bosnia.%20It%20is%20reported%20that%20he%20met%20a%20couple%20of%20Pakistani%20%26quot%3Bfighters%26quot%3B%20there%2C%20who%20introduced%20him%20to%20Maulana%20Masood%20Azhar%20upon%20his%20return%20to%20Pakistan.%20He%20trained%20in%20both%20Pakistan%20and%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20release%2C%20it's%20unclear%20where%20Sheikh%20went%20in%20Pakistan.%20According%20to%20some%20Pakistani%20papers%2C%20he%20lived%20in%20Lahore%2C%20where%20he%20married%20a%20local%20woman%20and%20had%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20this%20time%2C%20Omar%20Sheikh%20was%20known%20mostly%20to%20Indian%20investigators%20and%20intelligence%20communities.%20His%20name%20cropped%20up%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20release%20in%20December%201999%20from%20Tihar%2C%20but%20outside%20of%20India%2C%20he%20remained%20unknown.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Kidnapping%20Of%20Daniel%20Pearl%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20changed%20after%20the%20kidnapping%20of%20American%20journalist%20Daniel%20Pearl.%20Suddenly%2C%20everyone%20wanted%20to%20know%20who%20Sheikh%20was.%20A%20foreign%20media%20outlet%20published%20my%20encounter%20with%20him%2C%20and%20I%20was%20inundated%20with%20requests%20for%20interviews%20by%20the%20Western%20media.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESheikh%20was%20found%20guilty%20of%20kidnapping%20and%20murdering%20Pearl.%20He%20was%20given%20a%20death%20sentence%2C%20which%20was%20later%20turned%20into%20life%20imprisonment.%20According%20to%20a%20respected%20Pakistani%20journalist%2C%20who%20met%20a%20prison%20officer%20where%20Sheikh%20was%20lodged%2C%20Omar%20was%20shuttled%20regularly%20between%20Karachi%20and%20Hyderabad%20jails%2C%20spending%20a%20fortnight%20in%20each.%20The%20officer%20told%20the%20journalist%20that%20it%20was%20necessitated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20used%20his%20gift%20of%20the%20gab%20and%20often%20cast%20his%20spell%20on%20prison%20officials%2C%20who%20would%20then%20do%20him%20favours%2C%20like%20smuggling%20cellphones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Sheikh%20Posed%20As%20Pranab%20Mukherjee%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20precisely%20this%20gift%20that%20once%20landed%20the%20authorities%20into%20hot%20water%20and%20led%20to%20a%20near%20diplomatic%20crisis%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan.%20A%20year%20after%20the%202008%20Mumbai%20terror%20attacks%2C%20Karachi's%20Dawn%20newspaper%20ran%20an%20investigative%20story%20claiming%20that%20Sheikh%20had%20called%20the%20Pakistani%20President%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Asif%20Zardari%2C%20claiming%20to%20be%20India's%20then-foreign%20minister%20Pranab%20Mukherjee.%20It%20was%20reported%20that%20he%20used%20unparliamentary%20language%20on%20the%20call%20and%20threatened%20Zardari%20with%20dire%20consequences%20for%20the%20Mumbai%20attacks.%20The%20English%20daily%20claimed%2C%20%26quot%3BOmar%20Saeed%20Sheikh%2C%20a%20detained%20Pakistani%20militant%2C%20had%20made%20hoax%20calls%20to%20President%20Asif%20Ali%20Zardari%20and%20the%20Chief%20of%20Army%20Staff%2C%20Gen%20Ashfaq%20Parvez%20Kayani%2C%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20heighten%20Pakistan-India%20tensions%20after%20last%20year's%20terrorist%20attacks%20on%20Mumbai%2C%20investigators%20have%20told%20Dawn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20diplomatic%20crisis%20was%20averted%20after%20the%20call%20was%20traced%20to%20his%20cell%20in%20Hyderabad%20jail.%20The%20cell%20was%20raided%2C%20and%20it%20was%20found%20that%20Sheikh%20used%20a%20British%20SIM%20card%20to%20make%20the%20threatening%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Daniel%20Pearl's%20wife%2C%20Mariane%20Pearl%2C%20writing%20a%20book%2C%20titled%20A%20Mighty%20Heart%2C%20and%20despite%20the%20book%20being%20made%20into%20a%20Hollywood%20film%20with%20the%20same%20title%2C%20the%20story%20of%20Omar%20Sheikh%20remains%20shrouded%20in%20mystery.%20In%20dozens%20of%20court%20appearances%2C%20he%20often%20appeared%20affable%20and%20charming%2C%20but%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20his%20terror%20connections%20have%20been%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOmar%20Sheikh%20Is%20Still%20A%20Mystery%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20dictator%20Pervez%20Musharraf%20called%20him%20a%20British%20spy%20in%20his%20autobiography.%20Omar%20himself%20boasted%20of%20his%20deep%20links%20to%20Pakistan's%20Inter-Services%20Intelligence%20(ISI)%20in%20his%20off-the-cuff%20remarks%20to%20journalists%20during%20court%20hearings.%20He%20was%20known%20to%20have%20good%20relations%20with%20Jaish-e-Mohammed's%20Maulana%20Masood%20Azhar%20and%20Lashkar-e-Toiba's%20Zaki-ur-Rehman%20Lakhvi.%20Some%20journalists%2C%20who%20investigated%20the%20roles%20terror%20outfits%20played%20in%20the%20%C2%A09%2F11%20attacks%2C%20claimed%20he%20was%20an%20operative%20of%20Al-Qaeda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOmar%20is%20being%20held%20in%20jail%20despite%20his%20release%20order%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Pakistan.%20It%20is%20believed%20the%20country%20has%20kept%20him%20in%20prison%20after%20re-arresting%20him%20because%20of%20international%20pressure.%20But%20some%20also%20claim%20that%20he%20is%20better%20off%20in%20jail%2C%20lest%20he%20reveal%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725611820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fakm-img-a-in.tosshub.com%2Findiatoday%2Fimages%2Fstory%2F202004%2Fomar_shiekh_reuters_0.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fic-814-row-and-my-chance-encounter-with-a-global-terrorist-6503645%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Netflix%20web%20series%20IC%20814%3A%20The%20Kandahar%20Hijack%20has%20sparked%20a%20controversy%20over%20names%20of%20a%20few%20of%20the%20hijackers.%20But%20it%20has%20taken%20me%20back%20to%20my%20chance%20encounter%20with%20Omar%20Sheikh%2C%20one%20of%20the%20three%20terrorists%20released%20after%20the%20hijack.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fic-814-row-and-my-chance-encounter-with-a-global-terrorist-6503645%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2